1. docker container run --publish 80:80 nginix
the above creates a container of nginix server pulled from dockerhub
runs in foregroung

2. docker container run --publish 80:80 --detach nginix

creats the container and runs in the background

3. docker container ls -a

shows the containers

4. docker container rm containerid

to remover the container

5.  docker container rm -f container id

removes the container forcefully

6. docker container run --publish 80:80 --detach --name ravi nginix

runs the container with our specified name
#################################################

logs

to check the logs of running container

7. docker container logs
8. docker container logs name/container id

9. dcoker  top name/container id

to check the process in the container
